item.description: The Himalayan range is one of the youngest mountain ranges on the planet and have the third largest deposit of ice and snow in the world, after Antarctica and the Arctic. The Himalayan range encompasses about 15,000 glaciers, which store about 12,000 cubic km(3,000 cubic miles) of fresh water that sustains life with its natural bounty. Theo Organics farms are located 6,837 feet above sea level in the pristine environs of The Himalayas. The air, water and soil is at its natural best and we source our produce using traditional methods that have been handed down over centuries. Theo Organics Products retain the freshness and natural flavors of the mighty Himalayas
